Consider the topological space X = {1, 2, 3} with topology T = {{}, {1,2}, {1}}. Determine whether the following sets are open or closed in X:

1. {1}
2. {2}
3. {3}
4. {1, 2}
5. {2, 3}
6. {1, 2, 3}

Note: An open set is a subset of X that is a member of the topology T, and a closed set is the complement of an open set in X.
